<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn210">  210  Richard Ellmann, <cite>James Joyce</cite> (Oxford University Press, New York &amp; London, 1959), page 22. Joyce makes some brief references to his father's story in the notebooks: e.g. <a name="n22021b" href="../fnbs/n22all.htm#n22021b">N22 (VI.B.17):021(b)</a>. His seed idea of extending this to cover the conversion of the Norsemen is noted in N48 (VI.B.38).094: &lsquo;Viking into Xian.&rsquo;  </div>
